3k &= \frac{-3}{a - 30}\tag{2}\newline
5k &= \frac{-5}{a - 30}\tag{3}\newline
dk &= \frac{2}{a - 30}\tag{4}\newline
\end{split}
$
Let's use equations (2) and (3) to cancel $k$ and find the constant $a.$ Subtracting (2) from (3)
\begin{split}
3k + 5k &= \frac{-3}{a - 0} + \frac{-5}{a - 0}\newline
&= \frac{-8}{a - 0}\\
&= \frac{2}{a - 30}
\end{split}

This implies that $a = 32.$ Now you have a limit $d,$ which you can easily calculate using equation (1).
\end{split}
</think> $answer = \left(d, k\right)$ <answer> $\left(21, \frac{1}{32}\right)$ </answer>

